The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                Power supply may be affected on Friday in Auckland Square, Lower Circular Road, Moira Street, Minto Park, Beckbagan, Rawdon Street, Robinson Street and Shakespeare Sarani areas between 9.30am and 11.30am because of maintenance work by CESC.    Smoke was seen billowing from an electrical circuit box near the VIP lift gate of Lalbazar on Thursday afternoon. The box caught fire after a short-circuit, said Vineet Goyal, the deputy commissioner of police (headquarters). The fire was put out in 20 minutes.    The state government issued a notice to Kali puja organisers on Thursday that before collecting subscriptions, they will have to submit a list of collectors and a sample receipt to local police stations.    Shantanu Chakrabarty and a woman with whom he was allegedly having an extra-marital affair were arrested in Mumbai on Thursday following a complaint by his wife that he had stolen gold ornaments and Rs 1 lakh from his Khardah home.                                                                                                                                                              
